headline: Paychex forecasts upbeat full-year results, but quarterly profit falls
summary: HR software firm Paychex forecast full-year revenue and profit above Wall Street estimates on Wednesday, but its $4.1 billion acquisition of rival Paycor dragged down fourth-quarter profits. Shares of the company were down 9%. High interest rates and a volatile macro economy have pressured growth at human capital management firms such as Paychex that depend on small and midsize businesses.
